  Locus:
    Date: 19 June 2009
    Section: 44
---
Waves roughen the sea and windmill turn because of the wind. Take away the
wind and the sea becomes calm and the windmills come to rest. For every
effect there is a cause.

The waves of desire for things in the material world churn our minds, keep
up in a constant state of agitation, scrambling in all directions. What do
you think could happen if we eliminate desire?
